      "content": "In some jurisdictions, a lack of formal stability or education, especially when tied to urban poverty, can be framed by a judge as a lack of respect for the law or a failure to make better choices. The prosecution might argue that the environment fostered a criminal mindset, making the defendant less amenable to rehabilitation. Furthermore, some judges may hold a subconscious bias that individuals from disadvantaged backgrounds are inherently more prone to criminal behavior, leading them to view the circumstances as an aggravating element rather than a mitigating one.",
